23/04/2010
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- More than a dozen Romanian police officers assigned to EULEX were suspended from the mission Thursday (April 22nd), for allegedly smuggling cigarettes and alcohol. Mission chief Yves de Kermabon and Brussels officials insisted that the group of 16 policemen be relieved of their duties their jobs but allowed Bucharest to announce the suspensions. The Romanians were caught in possession of 341 cartons of cigarettes and 133 litres of alcohol while entering Macedonia this week. (Koha Ditore, Zeri, Express, Kosova Sot - 23/04/10; TV21, RTK - 22/04/10)
